# CVE-2026-41254 — liblcms2-2 (Little CMS) in distroless/java21-debian12 base
#
# Source: Google distroless base image (gcr.io/distroless/java21-debian12:nonroot)
# Fix:    Debian 12 backport 2.14-2+deb12u1 — already in debian-security but
#         the distroless image has not yet been rebuilt to pick it up.
# Risk:   The Little CMS library is not exercised by the JVM workload in any
#         of our services (no image / colour-profile processing in transaction,
#         account, accounting, auth or gateway). Information-disclosure and DoS
#         vectors require an attacker-controlled colour profile to reach lcms2,
#         which has no code path in this platform.
# Action: Re-evaluate when distroless rebuild lands; remove this entry then.
CVE-2026-41254
